tables.table_schema:
CREATE TABLE training_weather (
    training_session_id UUID PRIMARY KEY,
    date DATE,
    temperature FLOAT,
    humidity FLOAT,
    wind_speed FLOAT,
    performance_rating INT
);

CREATE TABLE training_sessions (
    session_id INT PRIMARY KEY,
    date DATE,
    weather_condition VARCHAR(50),
    duration_minutes INT,
    performance_score FLOAT
);

CREATE TABLE training_plans (
    plan_id INT PRIMARY KEY,
    goal VARCHAR(100),
    duration_weeks INT,
    recommended_sessions_per_week INT,
    impact_on_performance VARCHAR(200)
);

CREATE TABLE training_sessions (
  session_id INT PRIMARY KEY,
  date DATE,
  temperature DECIMAL(5,2),
  humidity DECIMAL(5,2),
  weather_conditions TEXT
)

CREATE TABLE performance_metrics (
  session_id INT PRIMARY KEY,
  athlete_id INT,
  average_speed DECIMAL(5,2),
  distance_covered DECIMAL(5,2),
  heart_rate INT
)

CREATE TABLE training_plans (
  plan_id INT PRIMARY KEY,
  target_distance DECIMAL(5,2),
  target_duration TIME,
  suggested_changes TEXT
)

CREATE TABLE TrainingSessions (
    session_id UUID PRIMARY KEY,
    date DATE,
    time TIME,
    location VARCHAR(255),
    temperature FLOAT,
    humidity FLOAT
)

CREATE TABLE Athletes (
    athlete_id UUID PRIMARY KEY,
    name VARCHAR(255),
    age INT,
    height FLOAT,
    weight FLOAT,
    team VARCHAR(255)
)

CREATE TABLE PerformanceMetrics (
    metric_id UUID PRIMARY KEY,
    session_id UUID,
    athlete_id UUID,
    avg_speed FLOAT,
    max_speed FLOAT,
    distance_covered FLOAT
)

CREATE TABLE WeatherForecast (
    forecast_id UUID PRIMARY KEY,
    date DATE,
    temperature FLOAT,
    humidity FLOAT,
    wind_speed FLOAT,
    description TEXT
)

CREATE TABLE TrainingPlans (
    plan_id UUID PRIMARY KEY,
    athlete_id UUID,
    date DATE,
    description TEXT,
    planned_distance FLOAT,
    intensity INT
)
